narratives.question_text: What was the name of your practicum instructor?
comments: The one and only Prof. Donyelle McCray!
Professor Tisdale was my Section leader and she was incredible!

narratives.question_text: What were her/his strengths or weaknesses?
comments: I am still in awe at how great an instructor she was. As nice as lecture was, I and my classmates are in agreement that section with Prof. McCray was the best part about this class. Her comments on my sermons were so detailed and helpful. Plus she did a masterful job governing section, even when the comments being given were... less than helpful.

Donyelle was exceptional. Her feedback was always valuable and helped push me to a different level. Our sections were well organized and efficient. She navigated several instances of tension in our section with great maturity.

Professor McCray was a great section leader. She created a supportive, encouraging environment that nonetheless allowed us to raise criticisms and challenge each other to grow. I appreciated the guidance and structure that she gave us for delivering feedback to one another.
Maria was very affirming in her feedback, while also offering constructive forms of criticism. She also used section times creatively to build on course material.
I described my experience in section in the narrative box above.
She had patience and really took us on an intimate journey with the scriptures. She gave room for everyone to be themselves and was always present when in need.
She is incredibly warm, encouraging, helpful, communicative, and constructive.
